Key Match Events: Pakistan won the toss and elected to bowl.
Australia won the match by 62 runs.
Shaheen Afridi took a five-wicket haul.
Rizwan was dismissed by Adam Zampa via DRS.
Iftikhar Ahmed was caught and run out.
Marcus Stoinis took a catch off Pat Cummins' bowling.
Post-Match Reflections: David Warner downplayed a groin injury concern.
Mark Taylor praised Australia's performance but noted room for improvement.
Australia has a four-day break before their next match.
